    • Method Detail

      • createUniqueName

        java.lang.String createUniqueName(Session session,
                                  java.lang.String baseName,
                                  @Nullable
                                  java.lang.String previousAttempt)
        Create a unique file name. This may be called multiple times for the same baseName.
        Parameters:
        session - session.
        baseName - the base name to incorporate in the file name.
        previousAttempt - if a prior call didn't generate a unique name, this method is called again with the result of the previous call. For the first call, this will be null.
        Returns:
        a possibly unique file name.
